<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1551" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1551">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/622.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to Consul <persName type="to">Alger</persName></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 290.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-29">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your
                                despatch No. 617 of May 22, 1915, in regard to the protest made by
                                you against the expropriation of the water plant at Mazatlan.</p>
                            <p>The Department approves the course pursued by you in this matter.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Acting Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>